title: Hilton Head Criterium Series
description: A fast paced Criterium on Hilton Head Island.
course: A closed loop around the Hilton Head Island High School. 1.5K, or .92 Miles.
registration: Register online. $25 for your first race, then $10 each additional.
notes: While a safe course, this loop does have two rolling speed bumps. Large enough to easily ride over.
directions: From 95 - Take 278 through Bluffton onto Hilton Head Island. Continue on 278 and Left on Wilborn Rd. Park in School lot.

title: Blythewood Omnium: Presented by Cobblestone Park
Coastal Cyclists 2012 After the Bridge Run Ride
description:
Coastal Cyclists 2012 After the Bridge Run Ride

Join the Coastal Cyclists and Trek Bicycle Store of Mount Pleasant for the annual After the Bridge Run Ride! Leave your running shoes behind and ride from Awendaw Green and the Sewee Outpost into beautiful Charleston and Berkeley Counties.

A Coastal Cyclists mainstay - the annual After the Bridge Run Ride has multiple routes, plenty of SAG support and miles and miles of beautiful scenery, and an awesome post ride celebration with live music from Awendaw Green and a post ride meal and beverages!
course: 10, 25, 45, 65, and 100 mile options through the scenic Low Country of Charleston and Berkeley County.

title: HONOR RIDE Bluffton S.C.
description:
Brief Description
HONOR RIDES are one-day bicycle rides (not races) which are designed for people to come out and recognize those who have been injured or have/are serving in our military. HONOR RIDES

PARKING
Parking will be at the high school and signs will be posted where event registration and start location are.

Additional Information
Registration/Check in: OPENS at 7:45am the morning the day of the event. DAY OF REGISTRATION cost is $25.00 (PRE-REG is only 15.00 dollars until April 16th...)

More Information
Click here to view the event organizer\'s website

Online Donations
Click here to donate to Ride2Recovery- HONOR RIDES
